# Product Spec: Trellis

What Trellis is, feature by feature, pillar by pillar. The single
source of truth for what the product does, what it doesn't do,
and what's coming.

This document is long because Trellis is not a small product.
Read it in sections, not all at once.

---

## What Trellis is

Trellis is the operating system for families. A web-based
subscription app built on Next.js 14 (Pages Router) + Supabase +
Vercel + the Anthropic API, with Twilio for SMS.

Trellis gives a family a shared dashboard across 11 pillars of
household life. Every family member has a role. Every pillar has
its own tools, content, and context. Cy (AI steward) reads it all
and surfaces one thing at a time.

Subscribers pay $29/month or $290/year.

---

## The core user

**Primary user:** The household lead parent (often, but not
always, the mother). This is the person who carries the mental
load of family logistics. Trellis is their product first.

**Secondary user:** The other adult (partner, spouse, or
co-parent). Co-equal access. Their own login. Shared household
data.

**Tertiary users:** Kids, ages 5-12 primarily, with a teen
variant (13-17) coming later.

**Access model:**
- One family subscription
- Two adult accounts (can be reduced to one for single parents)
- Unlimited kid accounts under the household
- Everyone sees the same house, age-appropriately

---

## What Trellis isn't

- Not a social network
- Not a parenting advice platform
- Not a therapy or counseling service
- Not a religious or faith-based product (faith-respectful, not
  sectarian)
- Not a banking or payment platform (finance tooling, yes;
  banking, no)
- Not an educational curriculum (educational content lives in
  THWB, not Trellis)

