## The kid experience

The kid view is a different product. Designed for ages 5-12
(teens get a closer-to-adult variant later).

### Kid home screen
- Their name and avatar
- Today's routine (morning checklist with pictures)
- Today's chores
- Their SoboBucks balance
- Today's schedule (calendar events relevant to them)
- Family kudos feed (kind notes sent to them)

### Kid features

**Morning Routine:**
Pictorial checklist. Brush teeth, make bed, get dressed, eat
breakfast. Tap to complete. Small celebration animation. Tracked
in Pillar 04.

**Chores + Economy:**
Assigned chores appear with descriptions. Tap when done. Earn
SoboBucks. See balance grow. Save toward a goal (books, toys,
experiences — parent-approved catalog).

**Today For Me:**
Their calendar view. Filtered to events relevant to them. What
time practice is. When dinner is. When bedtime is.

**Family Kudos:**
Feed of kind notes from parents and siblings. Can send kudos to
others. No public comments, no public anything.

**Growing Journal:**
A private journal where kids can write about their day,
decorate with stickers, and parents can read if shared.

### What kids don't have access to
- Partnership pillar (fully hidden)
- Family finances (except their own SoboBucks balance)
- Cy's adult-oriented observations
- Anything flagged private

### Kid safety rules

- No chat with people outside the household
- No public profiles
- No social feeds
- No AI generation outside of light Cy prompts
- Parents control the account
- Kid content is always visible to parents
- No ads, ever
- No in-app purchases
- COPPA-compliant (kids under 13 always require parent consent)

