## The adult experience

### Home dashboard (the first screen adults see)

**Morning message from Cy:**
- Today's calendar overview
- The three things that matter today
- Any flagged items from other family members

**Pillar tiles:**
- 11 cards in a grid
- Each shows: pillar number, name, most recent activity, any
  pending items
- Tap any tile to enter the pillar

**Quick adds:**
- Add a task
- Add to shared grocery list
- Add to calendar

**Presence:**
- See when partner last logged in
- See kid activity summary

### Navigation

**Primary tabs (bottom on mobile, left on desktop):**
- Home (dashboard)
- Pillars (grid of all 11)
- Tasks (cross-pillar task view)
- Calendar (unified)
- Cy (direct chat)
- Settings

### Task system

**Every task has:**
- Title
- Owner (who's responsible)
- Due date (optional)
- Pillar tag (which pillar this belongs to)
- Priority (quadrant-style: urgent-important matrix)
- Status (not started, in progress, done, deferred)
- Notes
- Optionally attached to a project

**Task views:**
- Today
- This week
- By pillar
- By owner
- Projects

**Shared tasks:**
- Either adult can create, edit, complete
- Both see updates in real time
- Cy can suggest tasks but humans confirm

### Calendar

- Integrates with Google Calendar (both adults)
- Unified view
- Color-coded by pillar
- Kids' events filtered to their view
- Family Meeting is a recurring weekly event

### Content library

**Integrated into pillars.** Content sourced from The House We
Built (essays, podcast episodes, frameworks) appears inside
relevant pillars in Trellis.

Example: An essay Kendra writes about "How we structure Sunday
evenings" appears inside Pillar 04 (Time and Rhythms), under a
"Reading" or "Library" tab.

**Content types:**
- Essays (long-form written)
- Podcast episodes (embedded player)
- Frameworks (structured explanations)
- Videos (minimal in 2026)

**Delivery:**
- Published to THWB first
- Syndicated into Trellis pillars via admin interface
- Paid Trellis families get full library
- Non-subscribers can read on THWB (most of it free)

