## Technical architecture

### Stack
- **Framework:** Next.js 14 Pages Router (existing)
- **Database:** Supabase (PostgreSQL)
- **Hosting:** Vercel
- **Auth:** Supabase Auth (Google OAuth + email/password)
- **AI:** Anthropic API (Claude) via server-side calls
- **Messaging:** Twilio (SMS for reminders, optional)
- **Payments:** Stripe (coming July 2026)
- **Analytics:** Vercel Analytics
- **Error tracking:** Sentry (not yet wired up)

### Data model (high-level)

**Households:** The top-level unit. One subscription per household.

**Users:** Adults and kids within a household. Separate auth per user.

**Pillars:** Each household has all 11 pillars scaffolded. Features
activate as pillars go live.

**Tasks:** Belong to a household, tagged to a pillar, assigned to
a user, optionally grouped into projects.

**Calendar events:** Synced from external calendars, tagged to
pillars, visible per user role.

**Cy interactions:** Logged per household for context, not for
training. Fully private.

**Content items:** Essays, podcasts, frameworks. Sourced from
THWB CMS, served into Trellis pillars.

### Performance targets
- Time to First Byte: <200ms
- Largest Contentful Paint: <1.5s
- Interactive: <2s
- Cy response time: <5s for most queries

### Mobile strategy
- Progressive Web App (PWA) for v1
- Works on any modern mobile browser
- Native iOS/Android deferred to 2027

