## Privacy and data principles

### What we see
- Everything a household puts into Trellis
- Aggregated, anonymized metrics across all households

### What we don't see
- Individual message content of DMs (we don't have DMs)
- Anything outside Trellis (no email scraping, no social scraping)
- Kids' data beyond what parents configure

### What we do with data
- Serve the product (that's it)
- Improve the product via aggregated, anonymized metrics
- Support the family if they ask for help

### What we never do
- Sell data to third parties
- Train AI models on family data
- Share data across households
- Use data for advertising

### What families can do
- Export their entire household data as JSON
- Delete their household (30-day grace period, then permanent)
- Control kid data and permissions

